Former Crime Intelligence CFO Solly Lazarus has been sentenced to 10 years in prison, in the Pretoria Magistrates court on Wednesday. Courtesy of #DStv403 PRETORIA - Former Crime Intelligence CFO Solly Lazarus has been sentenced to 10 years in prison, in the Pretoria Magistrates court on Wednesday but was then granted leave to appeal and posted bail. Bail was set for R10,000. READ: Case against Mdluli can be reopened: police, NPA Last year, he was found guilty of corruption for using the unit's account to buy vehicles for himself and family members. His co-accused, Hein Barnard, was acquitted. Their former boss, ex-crime Intelligence unit head Richard Mdluli was sentenced to five years in prison on a kidnapping and assault case.